cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language generation using neural networks. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques for generating poetry. It could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the retrieval of relevant information from a large corpus of ancient Chinese prose. Finally, it may also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it can accept images as input for generating poetry.
